The Executive Secretary, Nigeria Christians Pilgrims Commission (NCPC), Rev. Dr. Yakubu Pam, said attacks on innocent Nigerians and increasing criminalities are threatening the peaceful co-existence of Nigeria. Rev. Pam disclosed this on Monday in Jos, at the Church of Christ in Nations (COCIN) Church, Hwolshe, during a thanksgiving by the Correspondentsâ€™ Chapel of the Nigeria Union of Journalists (NUJ), Plateau State Council. Pam said that journalists in Nigeria, by their role, could assist to proffer solutions to the numerous challenges, particularly insecurity confronting the country, urging them to be the guide of the citizens on the critical roles they play in fostering peace.